Shiso Pesto Somen Salad

4 oz somen noodles
5 bunches shiso leaves
3/4 c grapeseed oil
1/4 tsp salt
1/4 oz yuzu juice
1 tbsp lemon zest

Bring 2 quarts heavily salted water to a boil. Add noodles and stir once, then leave to cook until al dente. Strain and then plunge into an ice bath. Strain again and set aside, refrigerating until use. Combine shiso leaves, oil, and salt in a blender. Pulse until smooth. Dress noodles with shiso pesto, then mix in yuzu juice. Garnish with lemon zest and serve.
